[
    {
        "text": "Hi, I am Francis, ",
        "start": 5.601,
        "duration": 1.262
    },
    {
        "text": "the host of this show \"Cooking with Dog.\"",
        "start": 6.863,
        "duration": 2.504
    },
    {
        "text": "First, let’s make the ponzu sauce.",
        "start": 14.986,
        "duration": 2.792
    },
    {
        "text": "Cut the yuzu citruses in half ",
        "start": 18.45,
        "duration": 2.516
    },
    {
        "text": "and squeeze out the juice with a citrus juicer.",
        "start": 22.638,
        "duration": 3.173
    },
    {
        "text": "You can substitute any type of sour citrus for the yuzu.",
        "start": 27.85,
        "duration": 4.067
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, lemon or lime.  ",
        "start": 32.334,
        "duration": 2.656
    },
    {
        "text": "Measure out 75 to 100ml (2.5~3.4 fl oz) of the juice in a bowl.",
        "start": 38.217,
        "duration": 4.964
    },
    {
        "text": "Put the bonito flakes into a dressing bottle.",
        "start": 45.903,
        "duration": 2.941
    },
    {
        "text": "Drop in the kombu seaweed.",
        "start": 53.94,
        "duration": 1.895
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour in the yuzu juice, ",
        "start": 58.86,
        "duration": 1.859
    },
    {
        "text": "soy sauce ",
        "start": 63.281,
        "duration": 1.154
    },
    {
        "text": "and mirin.",
        "start": 67.794,
        "duration": 1.238
    },
    {
        "text": "Close the bottle, ",
        "start": 71.602,
        "duration": 1.921
    },
    {
        "text": "shake ",
        "start": 74.515,
        "duration": 1.126
    },
    {
        "text": "and mix the sauce well.",
        "start": 75.641,
        "duration": 1.637
    },
    {
        "text": "When rushed, let it sit for about 3 hours.",
        "start": 84.988,
        "duration": 3.611
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, let’s cut the vegetables.",
        "start": 89.921,
        "duration": 2.272
    },
    {
        "text": "Cut off the stem end of the carrot ",
        "start": 93.493,
        "duration": 2.563
    },
    {
        "text": "and remove the skin with a peeler.",
        "start": 97.081,
        "duration": 2.388
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, shave long thin strips of the carrot with the peeler.",
        "start": 104.902,
        "duration": 4.063
    },
    {
        "text": "Remove the stem of the shiitake mushrooms, ",
        "start": 116.68,
        "duration": 3.171
    },
    {
        "text": "make a cut into the caps ",
        "start": 119.851,
        "duration": 2.092
    },
    {
        "text": "and tear them in half.",
        "start": 121.943,
        "duration": 1.813
    },
    {
        "text": "Slice the long green onion using diagonal cuts.",
        "start": 129.209,
        "duration": 3.56
    },
    {
        "text": "Cut the mizuna greens into about 2 inch (6cm) pieces.",
        "start": 139.739,
        "duration": 3.772
    },
    {
        "text": "You can substitute any leafy vegetable that has a mild flavor.",
        "start": 143.511,
        "duration": 4.778
    },
    {
        "text": "Next, let’s prepare the buri, fresh yellowtail.",
        "start": 150.084,
        "duration": 4.158
    },
    {
        "text": "Slice the yellowtail into about one eighth inch (2~3mm) slices ",
        "start": 155.116,
        "duration": 3.727
    },
    {
        "text": "using diagonal cuts.",
        "start": 158.843,
        "duration": 1.954
    },
    {
        "text": "Line up the slices on a plate.",
        "start": 165.076,
        "duration": 2.172
    },
    {
        "text": "Next to the yellowtail, ",
        "start": 175.04,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "place the carrot, ",
        "start": 176.96,
        "duration": 1.073
    },
    {
        "text": "shiitake, ",
        "start": 178.033,
        "duration": 1.345
    },
    {
        "text": "long green onion ",
        "start": 182.047,
        "duration": 2.523
    },
    {
        "text": "and mizuna greens.",
        "start": 184.57,
        "duration": 1.786
    },
    {
        "text": "And now, let’s cook the Buri Shabu-Shabu!",
        "start": 187.777,
        "duration": 2.854
    },
    {
        "text": "Pour the dashi stock and kombu seaweed ",
        "start": 196.522,
        "duration": 2.369
    },
    {
        "text": "into a pot ",
        "start": 198.891,
        "duration": 1.37
    },
    {
        "text": "and turn on the burner.  ",
        "start": 201.485,
        "duration": 1.841
    },
    {
        "text": "Meanwhile, pour the homemade ponzu sauce into a bowl ",
        "start": 205.819,
        "duration": 4.231
    },
    {
        "text": "and add the grated daikon radish ",
        "start": 210.05,
        "duration": 2.327
    },
    {
        "text": "and chopped spring onion leaves.",
        "start": 212.377,
        "duration": 2.243
    },
    {
        "text": "Just before the stock begins to boil, ",
        "start": 217.893,
        "duration": 2.994
    },
    {
        "text": "remove the kombu seaweed.",
        "start": 220.887,
        "duration": 1.92
    },
    {
        "text": "Add the sake ",
        "start": 226.77,
        "duration": 1.418
    },
    {
        "text": "and the salt, ",
        "start": 229.777,
        "duration": 1.19
    },
    {
        "text": "and stir.",
        "start": 234.09,
        "duration": 1.34
    },
    {
        "text": "Place the carrot and shiitake into the pot.",
        "start": 240.152,
        "duration": 3.126
    },
    {
        "text": "Then, add the long green onion and mizuna greens.",
        "start": 246.381,
        "duration": 3.924
    },
    {
        "text": "And here is the rice cake for shabu-shabu.",
        "start": 252.959,
        "duration": 2.628
    },
    {
        "text": "Now, using a pair of chopsticks, ",
        "start": 257.104,
        "duration": 4.001
    },
    {
        "text": "stir the yellowtail in the hot broth, ",
        "start": 261.105,
        "duration": 2.879
    },
    {
        "text": "dip it into the ponzu sauce ",
        "start": 263.984,
        "duration": 2.598
    },
    {
        "text": "and enjoy the buri shabu.",
        "start": 266.582,
        "duration": 1.919
    },
    {
        "text": "We recommend not to cook the fresh buri too much, ",
        "start": 272.632,
        "duration": 3.18
    },
    {
        "text": "leaving the inside rare to medium rare.",
        "start": 275.812,
        "duration": 3.057
    },
    {
        "text": "This is a healthy hot pot with lots of vegetables.",
        "start": 279.805,
        "duration": 3.443
    },
    {
        "text": "Store the ponzu in the fridge.",
        "start": 283.746,
        "duration": 2.562
    },
    {
        "text": "As time passes, it will taste milder, ",
        "start": 286.308,
        "duration": 3.345
    },
    {
        "text": "making the sauce more delicious.",
        "start": 289.653,
        "duration": 2.203
    },
    {
        "text": "You can also strain the ponzu sauce ",
        "start": 296.424,
        "duration": 2.337
    },
    {
        "text": "to remove the kombu seaweed and bonito flakes.",
        "start": 298.761,
        "duration": 3.604
    },
    {
        "text": "Good luck in the kitchen!",
        "start": 303.035,
        "duration": 1.657
    }
]